12/11/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Defence Minister Ioan Mircea Pascu and his Greek counterpart, Yiannos Papantoniou, signed a bilateral protocol for military co-operation in 2004, during Papantoniou's visit to Bucharest on Tuesday (11 November). 
The document envisions concrete forms of bilateral activities as well as boosting the interoperability of the respective armed forces. 
Papantoniou also reiterated his country's support for Romania's entry into NATO and the EU. 
(ACT Media - 12/11/03; Rompres, BBC, ANA - 11/11/03)
